    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; DT, 9 and 10 Engine Service Manual - Crankcase, Crankshaft, and
        Camshaft - Removal - Oil Level Gauge Assembly
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Oil Level Gauge Assembly</title>
        <figure id="f3350016501" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figk06/k06019.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Oil level gauge assembly</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil filler tube support</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M6 x 40 bolt and M6 nut</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Tube clamp</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil level gauge tube</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil filler tube</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Cushioned clamp</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para id="s1602" count="1">Remove M6 x 40 bolt and M6 nut securing the oil filler tube to the oil filler
                tube support.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen tube clamp and remove the oil filler tube assembly from the oil level gauge tube.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If required, remove the oil filler tube support. Remove two M8 nuts and one M6 x 16 bolt
                holding the oil filler tube support to the fuel filter header and remove the
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_170.xml" xrefid="s0707">low-pressure fuel pump outlet tube assembly</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s0707"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If required, remove the oil level gauge tube by driving the tube up and out of the crankcase
                using a brass punch and hammer.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
